  "label": "Sootlamp Sleeping Alcove",
  "description": "Sootlamp Sleeping Alcove is a narrow berth-room cut into the slagcrete mass of Sootlamp Quarters, its walls coated in vitrified sealant to resist ash infiltration. A fold-down bunk and recessed storage lockers sit flush to the surfaces, leaving a clear decontamination strip along the floor. The only illumination comes from a shielded lumen-slit that throws bruise-violet highlights across soot-dark panels and gasketed seams. A muffled ventilation grille and grit-trap housing dominate one corner, emphasizing the hab’s dependence on filtration and sealed air.",
